\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 36. P. capitatum} Buch.-Ham. ex D. Don, {\i Prodr. Fl. Nepal. }73 (1825). Glandular-pubescent perennial. Stems up to 30 cm, decumbent, rooting at the lower nodes. Leaves 20-50 × 10-25 mm, ovate to elliptical, acute. Inflorescence 5-10 mm, capitate, dense; peduncles 10-30 mm. Perianth pink; nut c. 2 mm, trigonous.{\i  Cultivated for ornament, and naturalized in Açores and N. Portugal}. [Az Lu.] ({\i Himalaya}.)
\par

