\pard\f0\fs28 Sect. BISTORTA (Scop.) D. Don. Perennial herbs with short, stout rhizomes. Ochreae brown, not lacerate. Flowers in fairly dense, terminal spikes. Perianth petaloid; stamens 6-8; styles 3, long and slender. Nut trigonous.
