\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 38. P. bistorta} L.,{\i  Sp. Pl.} 360 (1753). Rhizome stout, contorted. Stems 20-100 cm, erect, simple. Lower leaves 5-15 cm, ovate, obtuse, truncate at base; petioles long, broadly winged in upper part. Upper leaves triangular-lanceolate, acute or acuminate. Flowers bright pink, in a dense, cylindrical, terminal spike 20-70 × 10-15 mm. Nut 4-6 mm, glossy. 2n = 44.{\i  Damp, grassy places. Throughout a large part of Europe, but only on mountains in the south and absent as a native from most of Fennoscandia.} Al Au Be Br Bu Cz Ga Ge Gr He Ho Hs Hu It Ju Lu Po Rm Rs (N,B,C,W,K,E) [Da *Fe Hb No Su].
