\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 39. P. amplexicaule} D. Don, {\i Prodr. Fl. Nepal.} 70 (1825). Stems 60-100 cm, erect. Leaves large, ovate-acuminate, cordate; the lower petiolate, the upper sessile-amplexicaul. Flowers deep red, in dense but rather slender, cylindrical spikes. Nut 4-5 mm, rarely produced in Europe.{\i  Cultivated for ornament, and naturalized in Britain and Ireland.} [Br Hb.] ({\i Himalaya.})
