\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 41. P. alpinum} All.,{\i  Mélang. Philos. Math. Soc. Roy. Turin} ({\i Misc. Taur}.) {\b 5:} 94 (1774) ({\i P. undulatum} Murray). Stems 30-80 cm, erect, arising from a short, creeping underground rhizome. Leaves 10-30 mm wide, oblong-lanceolate, tapered at both ends. Ochreae mainly hyaline, soon disappearing. Flowers white or pale pink, in a diffuse panicle. Perianth-segments subequal. Styles very short, with large capitate stigmas. Nut 4-5 mm, exceeding the perianth, trigonous, pale brown, glossy.{\i  Usually calcifuge. S., C. & E. Europe, mainly in the mountains.} Al Au Bu Co Ga Gr He Hs It Ju Rm Rs(*N, C, W, E) [Br Da]
