\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 44. P. campanulatum} Hooker fil.,{\i  Fl. Brit. India}{\b  5:} 51 (1886). Stoloniferous; stems up to 100 cm, erect, much branched, stout. Leaves 5-12 × 2-4 cm, lanceolate to ovate or ovate-elliptical, cuneate at the base, acute, with conspicuous whitish to pinkish-brown tomentum beneath. Inflorescence a compact, terminal panicle; flowers heterostylous. Perianth 4-5 mm, pink or white; nut c. 2 mm, brown, glossy, included in the perianth.{\i  Cultivated for ornament, and naturalized in Britain and Ireland}. [Br Hb.] ({\i Himalaya and W. China}.)
